<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghogue, Huber &amp; Rutish., Nordic J. Bot. 31 (4): 458" authorityYear="2013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Djinga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Djinga cheekii" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cheekii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Djinga cheekii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not listed on the http://www.iucnredlist.org. The taxon is known only from the type locality, Mantem River near Manjo. The extent of occurrence is estimated as 4 km2, and area of occupancy is about 4 km2. The main threat at the locality is agriculture. Based on this threat, and the continuous decline of vegetation cover in the area, extent and /or quality of habitat the taxon is here assessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB1+2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
